cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial action unit detection and face alignment, which are both tasks related to computer vision. Additionally, the use of deep learning frameworks further supports this categorization. The paper also involves the use of adaptive attention learning, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of benchmarks for evaluation suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the focus on facial expressions and emotions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
